\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid1250662 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 I should say thirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Thirty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you know where your father came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You don't know the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh. Town. He come from Farnworth. Yes.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 He were a plate layer. Yes, a plate lay
er on't' railway. And got seventeen and tenpence a week and - and - when he - when he got some over time, say, what we called fogging - yes, they put big cats on line for - just before like they enter station, you see, to slow 'em down and then when he ha
d his overtime paid to him it were paid with - a - a chip and he had to go and get some either egg or bacon or pork chops or something like that, they didn't give you money for - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Your father was always a plate layer was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Can you remember him doing any other job or any part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well he only - he went to playing at public houses, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 As a part time job did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. At nights and - and at weekends and - he - he got so used to - drinking beer you know, like
 - it'd always like - he'd play for anybody and there'd - then they'd all say, water player. And by time he - from home he'd - he were drunk. Well - one night he come home and you always had to wait up for him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You did - your mother did?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. A
nd me. And we had a - what you call sofa. Only one arm on and this 'ere one arm it led to - cupboard. Me father starts undressing himself downstairs, next thing he's walking up into cupboard for go to bed, I've to pull him - pull him back with shirt.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 He was so drunk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So drunk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you remember your father ever being }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 out}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  of work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. No. And then like - I used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 laugh about}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  - in the morning when he were going to his work. About seven o'clock, I always remember it. He'd shout upst
airs, me mother's name were Alice, he'd shout upstairs, Alice, send us threeha'pence down for a pint. She says, I'll give you no threeha'pence. So }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 if}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  he'd go and he'd bang door, nearly knock it off its hinges. Then - another day or two after his - he'd ple
ad again for this 'ere threeha'pence for a pint. Me mother'd open her heart and give it him. But it were different now, no banging of door, it was this, good-morning Alice luv.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 When he got his threeha'pence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Threeha'pence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did your mother work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
We had a little - shop. It were on corner of Lee Street and Campbell Street and she sold bits of grocery and then at night it were - she had kitchen and - like a chip shop. And we used to go - yes, and then on top of that she had one of them}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149  there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  machines - wooden machines you know, what you could refoot stockings on. They used to have them refooted and all like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And your mother did all of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So she ran the shop during the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, and then chip shop at night. Yes, same place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And she refooted stockings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 If - if there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 any come, yes.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 However did she manage it all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh she was very good but - me father, he were - he was just a drag. I mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well, for instan
ce, he'd - he used to drink like this and then next time we'd - there'd be men as me mother know'd very well'd be walking backwards and forwards up at shop and - finish she said - what's - keep walking up and down here for? Does he owe you sommat? So fath
er said how much he owed him and - she had pay him, now when father comes home and she says, so and so's been, I've paid him, he said he didn't owe it him, you know. Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Was your mother a Farnworth woman too or did she come from somewhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 My mother come from place called Gravel Hole, Great Lever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why did they call it Gravel Hole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Because - it's - it's - nearly - all underneath's gravel. I mean it's quite a number of years since now, some houses collapsed in Fylde Street which 
a bit father up and all - and all where they call Gravel Hole it's honeycomb with roads from Bradford pit, that's on the Manchester Road. Up from Fylde to Bolton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So she was born between Farnworth and Bolton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 She - she - no, she was born in Gravel Hole.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What town was the Gravel Hole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Bolton. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And she worked all the time after she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2893269 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  then with the shop did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Yes, yes, she had this 'ere shop. Well see me father be eventually got - accident on lines and - h
e really - he died at thirty-nine. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Were you a big family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. There were only me sister and me. Now - when it - when he were off bad I used to - play wag from school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And get into trouble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. I - I played - I go - reckon go
 up first but I lie in a cart as allus was in back you see and my turn go back up to Francis Street School and then I'd come out. I'd better not mention this woman's name, I might - but - a - the lady used to come, they had a shop in - Egerton Street, I'l
l not name the shop, and - she liked a drop of rum and tea, so I knew that and I were waiting. Then she'd come across and - me father was in bed and I'm sitting at fire waiting, comes across, gives me sixpence ha'penny, sixpenny for her noggin of rum and 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 ha'penny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  for me for some toffees. They're drinking rum and tea and I be -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Your mother and this lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. Not me mother. Me mother's working now, at mill. She's working at mill now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 This was when you were older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, I'd be ten. Nine or
 ten. See mother was working at mill so - this 'ere woman comes across, gives us this 'ere sixpence ha'penny, I goes for this 'ere noggin of rum and ha'porth toffee myself. They're drinking rum and - rum and tea I'm eating toffee, everybody's happy. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How old were you when you went to school, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Oh yes. Yes. I - I went - I went to school and - used to pay tuppence - spending money. That wasn't - tuppence - tuppence a week, yes, used to pay tuppence a week. So one day I thought, o
h crumbs, I'm not going to school. I'm spending tuppence corner shop do you see. So I - I got two penn'orth of toffees then I went right down Francis Street, down Alpha Street and trains now runs from Moses Gate to Farnworth and I'm on 't' railings now ov
e
r there watching them and eating me toffees. All of a sudden there's a ballast man comes with a big - big truck on lines and they're mending you know and - eventually they beckon on me, say, here young 'un. So I went down and - fellow says, he says, you s
ee's all these men here? I says, yes. He says, that foreman. So - made me foreman. I haven't been foreman five minutes than they give me a couple of cans and two or three - and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 threepence}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 . He says, now go up there and over them - railings and down McDonald Street to that off }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 license}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  and get two pints of ale. I were beer carrier.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Instead of going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Yes. But I went - morning time ale. So at dinner time I - I went home for me dinner. When I come back, all these men, some had bit of cheese an
d bread left and - some beef and what - and they must have thought I had to eat 'em all up. Come on, get - have this young one, you know. But I kept on with this 'ere job and going over one morning I think this 'ere old woman must have been very sorry for
 me and she says to me, when I'm coming back she says, would like a piece of gooseberry pie? I says, yes please. And do you know, up to now I've never had no gooseberry pie as tasted as good as that as that old woman give me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How old were you when you started school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 When I started school? I'd be about five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What time did you start in the morning in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh eight - nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you stay all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, only you - you went home to your dinner. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What time would you finish at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 About half past four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What kind of school was it, was it a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, it were - congregation. Congregational church school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Was it boys and girls mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How did you get to school, you walked it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes, it weren't so far do you see, it weren't so far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you go on your own or did someone go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, I went on me own, yes. Me - Near - nearly all children them days had go on their own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you come home to your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Oh they didn't - they didn't take them in motor cars like they're doing 'em today. Had to walk it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What did you think of school when you were a child, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well - I - I told you I played wag but really I did like the school I went to 'cos we had some very good teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You liked the teachers did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes. Very good. Yes, I did, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Can you remember if the teachers when you were a child emphasised certain things as importan
t like manners or tidiness or punctuality or way of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well I don't remember, no, I don't remember them ever telling us that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you not remember anything that they told you was very important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. No. Don't no - no, I don't rem
ember them telling us anything like that. They just seemed to - give us these 'ere sums and that - what - what I did like about best were when we had reading, we did all Shakespeare. Yes. But - the - The Tempest and - Shylock, you know, we - we had some c
lass }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15296863\charrsid9517149 stuff.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Suppose you did something that the teachers didn't like, how did they punish you?
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\tx8100\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid1250662 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Well the - one lady when you were in th'infants she had a - a knuckle summat like that. A deformed - and she used to bump that into your back. Yes. And then one day, I don't know what I'd - I don't know - and this 'ere teachers, she struck at me and}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149  hit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  me against th'eye.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid1250662 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
And she hurt your eye?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, so I went home, I told me father and me father went and he seen her about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did they punish the girls the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What were the things that you mostly got punished for as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well - well I thought I hadn't - I didn't know that I'd done anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you remember what they did punish children for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Did punish them for fighting in th'yard or - you know - not coming out - if they're told to. We haven't we had - two lads at our school - who they couldn't do much with. One was - one -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Ay? They're - they're too big lads. One were - Whitelegg and t'other were Urmson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 They were very rough boys were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Oh yes. I mean, they could - they could turn - as - work - th'headmaster thought he could - give 'em a good hiding, they'd have him. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you ever see them hit the headmaster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Oh yes, them two could, oh yes. Aye. White - Whitelegg's - they were - they had a coal place there and they used to have all that there - renting dogs down for -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 For dog breeders. For dog breeders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 They bought dogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 If - if you had a fat dog and you wanted it destroyed they'd destroy it and they'd - render it down for dog grease.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What did they do with the dog grease?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh reckoned it were good thing for sprains and that. Yes. Yes. Oh it used to be good - aye, dog grease, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So if you didn't want your dog you took it to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You sold it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well you'd give it 'em and - they'd - destroy it and they'd boil it down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 They used to just boil it down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. W
ell now you see in them days people like who were bad on their chest I remember a fellow called Mr Hurst, an old fellow, said to - you'll - you'll not - you'll never live so long. Well his son started getting everybody's goose grease. And he could, and he
 lived - I don't know how long on goose grease, it didn't matter whether it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15296863\charrsid9517149 were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 burned or how it were, he got it down. Goose grease.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 But they never used dog grease for rubbing the chest did they, that was just for sprains?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 For sprains and that, 
yes, for - but whatsname - they eat - for - for - for having a bad chest they eat dog - goose grease. Yes. Yes. Well I mean to say you see, a lot of children in them days, I mean, they'd come in and say, I'm hungry mother. Well mother hadn't - hadn't real
ly much give 'em so give 'em about - a big thick slice of bread and jam and then say, get this pint of tea down luv. Now get that pint of tea down onto top of thick slice of jam and bread that'll sell.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You don't have a very good opinion of your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Well why I - why should I have? Well I mean if my father had pulled his weight - we - we wouldn't have been so bad. For instance, I mean to say, me grandfather Howe, they were all crofters. All crofters. And he were boss of this particular part. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 Now Smiths croft, I'm going back a while now aren't I - Smiths croft give grandfather Howe the chance of having all the fence. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
He didn't take them. The man as took them were Horrocks. That's Horrocks's today as you see in Hoseley Street. They started from fence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What did your granddad do as a crofter, tell me what his job was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 He - well I - as far as I know he were a boss over them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What did the crofters do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well, see, I - I can't - I've never been in a croft myself. No, I don't know wha
t they do. No. I mean at some crofts like - I remember one - at one croft called Champions - a fellow called Wilkinson he told me he says, what he did was this. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 
You are a manufacturer and you're}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9517149  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 sending goods out to India. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Now you send this material to me 
and I have now to stretch it out and make it more. So now to do this with your cloth I have squeezers and that as'll pull it out and I have to keep putting - china clay in. You know, keep clay to at finish it - it comes to you stiff. Well soon as you star
t washing it that china clay goes out it's like muslin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 This was called filling wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Yes. Well it's same with some of these - today. Some of these counterpanes you get today. They - no, they go through a hot solution of salts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You were telling me you liked the mini skirts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, well do you want me to tell you about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What you told me last week, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 the mini}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  skirts as against the old fashioned women, the way they dressed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes, yes. Yes, I mean, is it right now? I like
 the mini skirts because of one thing, they're very hygienic because - when you go back and think about - the ladies and wives in the old times when they used to - be wearing them long skirts and more times than not they couldn't have baths, they must hav
e stunk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You remember this do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. They must have. So that's why I like mini skirts, they look smarter, swell out and now they fill full.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you see a lot of hunger amongst children when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes, saw a bit of it
, yes. But I mean to say, them children eventually - when they come to work - get about seventeen or eighteen they just fade away like flowers. They haven't the stamina. They - they've not got - they've not been built on it, they've been built on jam and 
bread and tea. Never had a proper meal really. Now when they come for start doing summat - oh used to - there was a lot like that. I mean like we - we'd acquired our share of T.B. you know. Oh yes, in them days we had our share of T.B. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 This school that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did all the children come from the same type of homes or were there different types of children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh well - well the - there's - there - there were different types. Yes, like some thought they should be on third
 row and - which were best row. They - they used to have a few bit snobbish. Like anywhere else, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What was the difference between the snobbish children and the ordinary children, was it a better home or more money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well the - the - the - wel
l as far as the children were concerned there were satisfied with their home and they didn't think they were any better than 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why did you say that some children were snobbish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Because - the - there's a certain lot wanted to sit on - at one row. They kind of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 commandeered}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  that and if you tried to go on like they'd shove you off and one thing - you know what I mean, like - how they do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did the teachers ever treat some children specially, in a special way or favour them in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Wel
l - the - the - there only one girl treated in a special way. She were allowed to sit down all the time in school because her body were too heavy for her legs. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did she have some form of disease?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, but - no, she - she - she'd - she'
d a big body and she got tired with - stand - with stand - with holding that weight on her legs and they allowed her to -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you stand a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well you used to stand different parts of day and she had to sit down all the time. That's the only - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you ever have gangs or groups in your school as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. I mean I - I were with - I were with - I were with Urmson and - Whitelegg. Three of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You were in a gang were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, but I - I were - I were little lad. These two were big lads.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What did you do as a gang? Don't tell me you terrorized all the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
No, we didn't - we didn't terrorise the others. We just went about schooling, it were t'others as tried it on us. See anybody took advantage of me these
 two pals of mine, Whitehead and - whatsname - stepped in. I say otherwise - otherwise they looked after me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You don't remember any other gangs or groups in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. No. Not while - well see there were one of these two big lads, I know, a big
 tall lad come - to - to school - from Bury and a lad from Heywood come and - well - Whitelegg he were cock of our school, this - 'ere big lad from whatsname he - he come and he - he reckoned he were cock of all Bury and started on our neighbourhood and h
e - he wiped floor with him. And they were flags you know. Aye, flagstones yard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you remember any children being left out of things at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, I don't remember. No. Everybody seemed they could participate in anything. Oh yes, no they were - they were nothing like that. No.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did your mum and dad take an interest in your school, did they ask - ever visit the school or go to see the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 They hadn't the time. Yes, they hadn't the time, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Were all he children the same class of people as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Yes, they - 'cos - there weren't much difference really I mean to say - if a fellow got twenty-six shillings a week than he didn't take his jacket off you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did this mean he was a boss?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
He were boss. Yes. Yes. And - like you - you know the reputation of Lancashire don't you? Well the reputation of Lancashire was - that the parents were the only - Lancashire was the only county where the parents lived in the young. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How did they live on the young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
The - they'd get about six o - seven children, now they don't - they don't bother where they're going to finish, they shove 'em out into pit or into mill where they can get some money. They don't bother about where they're going to 
finish up. Yes, it - it was the only county where the parents lived in their young. Lancashire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What age were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Would you have stayed longer if you could have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 To tell you the truth I - I don't really know. I couldn't tell you. Perhaps it - they'd not have informed me if I'd stayed on longer then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you think you benefited from your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes. Oh yes, I mean but for - but for education all these people that are here today they'd be as numb as addlers. Addlers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Them big - things you see flying about that - long body like that and that, sharp wings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Sort of dragon flies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Addlers, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Have you any regrets about your education looking back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. Because I tell you, it were a good school I went to and I liked the teachers there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You only went to just the one school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, I - I finished last two - two years at a church school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Which school was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 That were - A
ll Saints. And they had a lady there as were th'headmistress. And I found out the difference. I found - I found - I found out the difference of education when I landed there. I weren't one of best at Francis Street, I were just ordinary. But when I got to
 - All Saints, I were one of best - one of best or one of - if you do - one as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 does}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 the sums first or does this first, they can go out to play as soon as they've done it. I - I had me hand up and I were allus going out first - first and within - blotting paper going - Great Britain - flag of Great Britain on, one thing and another.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Was there a lot of difference in this school, was it a boys and girls school just the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well, that's right, yes, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Was it far from home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, no, no. 
No, because we'd moved down there do you see, we'd moved to a house there which were - it were - the rent were only three shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What was the difference in the two schools, did you like the teachers there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes, I liked the teachers there but - it seemed easier. Didn't seem - and it must have been for me to - do it so free. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you remember anything they emphasised as important at this school, anything that they taught you at this second school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, they didn't - they never ta
ught you anything properly, just give you your - you know, whatsname but - the - they taught - they taught 'em - oh - they used to have religious read - reading when you went in you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 In the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. So - well we didn't have that at Fra
ncis Street. No. And I allus said to myself, I'm not going to be a parson so why should I carry on with this rubbish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You didn't like it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. So when I went - All Saints where they had it I sat down when they're doing it. He says, stand up. I s
ays, I'm not - I'm not bothering in this stuff, I says, I've come from other school, we didn't have it there and I'm not - I won't start at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 this}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  time neither. I'm not going to do it. He said nothing. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did they punish you at this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. They daren't have punished me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did they punish children at this school at all though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 At All Stains? At - at whatsname. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did they never punish children there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 They daren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Because they - they used to gang - there us
ed to be about four or five in a gang and as soon as you were doing with teacher and you come round to - said to me, Wolfendale get up, there'd be four more gang up with me too, with their fists like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 They were all big boys were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. And you'd go - you'd go back and say, you soft cakey. Which it - never hit anybody - daren't hit anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Your teachers were frightened were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well you - you show them. And - when - when whatsname come - circus used to come to Farnworth mark
et someone'd say, we'd be out playing at, you know, playtime. Someone'd say, hey circus has gone up - Bolton Road, go to old market. Hey. We went. Left school. Didn't go back for afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Didn't you get into trouble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 I told - they - no, they daren't touch -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did they never send home for your mother and dad or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Sent us home? Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you like this school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. And then one day I went and I think my clogs weren't so - clean. Says, go back and clean y
our clogs. I went back and never went school that day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you have to pay at this school too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, I didn't pay at church school. No. Didn't pay at church schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You liked the teachers here did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes. I mean like - the best schools in Farnworth at that time I tell you were Francis Street and Wesleyans. T'other two - they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why were they the best schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well - they - it were harder work for doing sums and that. These other two - St Tomas's and All Saints, they - they seemed - too easy.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Too easy going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, the stuff as you had, it wasn't - it didn't seem as hard. That's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you remember gangs in this second school that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. There about - about five of us. They sit all on one form. A
nd when she said, come out - go out and go to th'headmistress, you - you just wouldn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 budge}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Then what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 If she'd come we'd all sit up - well up. If you get five standing up you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You were a little terror weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. No, you - I'm without father now you know. And them as without father he used to rap at 'em in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Your father had died then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why did they rap at them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well it - it - it says it better for themselves now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why did they rap at them if they had no father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
They - they - they didn't seem to think that they were anybody that - back 'em up. You couldn't - couldn't go and say, I'll bring me father. You - you were what - anybody without father he - he turned out to be ch
eeky, ignorant and every - thing that's wrong because he had to stick up for himself. Otherwise these others'd have just have wiped the floor with him. When you - when you - when a child has support of his mother and father it's worth something. But when 
you're father - when you've no father and these had fathers and mothers they - they come on to you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So you learnt to fight for yourself very early?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. You. Anybody - any boy that is left without father you'll find out that he has to fight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Your mother worked didn't she after you children were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Who looked after you while she was working? You say she went to the mill later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, she went to the mill, well she - she went to mill and - she used come home
 at half past twelve 'til half past one so she used to get our meals ready at night and Fidians mill were only a matter about five minutes from t'house, see. So we all had our meal together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How old did you say you were when your father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Which was the house you lived in longest as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Wait a minute. Wait a minute. Wait a minute. No. I lived - I lived in longest in shop. As a child. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How many rooms were there at this shop and how did you live in them, what sort of rooms were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Well like - I remember - there must have been a few bedrooms because - textile mill were built there and we'd two men as were - lodgers and we'd a - a lady - young lady from - Nott End, as a servant. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What did she do, what was her job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well she helped me mother in shop and - and chip shop and everything do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did she live in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. She lived in, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What did you cal her, how did you speak to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 I couldn't just say. Either she would - would call her with her name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You were only tiny were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You don't remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. Well I don't - I - we left when I was ten. So I've no idea, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So where did you and your sister sleep if you had lodgers in the house, where would you and your sister and mother and dad sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
We must have had a - a tidy few rooms. I mean to say, with them two lodgers and with that lady, that's three, four five, six, seven of us and I don't - Oh I remember. I used to sleep with on of lodgers. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And your sister slept with who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well perhaps she slept with young lady, any. That were only way wasn't it. Yes. Because - I remember - when }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 I\rquote m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  - when I went to work - when I were at Co-op there and I went - the - this - work - in caf\'e9, working in 't' caf\'e9
 and a lad come up and - said, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 hello}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 . Good morning. He said, do you want any? So - Ernie says.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 This was when you were a by when you were working, this boy came to the Co-op to ask for a job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. He - yes, and he - he come -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And he found out his mum and dad didn't want him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Not really want him because they'd a two bedroomed house and there's his mother and father and these two sisters which had turned into young women. Well - where they going to put - where
 are they going to put Albert. He's come now to age, he's a funny age. He can't sleep with sisters can he.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So what happened to Albert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So - he - kept on 'til he were eighteen and then he joined Navy for twelve year. That's all he could do. He wa
sn't wanted. They hadn't room for him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 He used to tell you this did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
He'd no need tell us. And - me mother used say - her husband her husband, oh how bad he were and he wanted work you know but - Albert got free food in caf\'e9 so what did his 
mother do? She told him to take his wage and have it put in her book in Co-op. Her were all right weren't she? It were a husband she said as were bad 'un but she were having his wage put to her account at Co-op.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 This lady who worked for your mother, do you know what hours she worked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well, as she went - eventually when she left us she - went to working for a solicitor. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you know what hours she worked for your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well you see, in them days - you - you kind of got up, started
 and you - you kept on. Unless - unless you wanted go somewhere. I remember this 'ere young lady as we had she went over onto Manchester Road working for a solicitor and - me mother went one day somewhere to had - to same }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 place where}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  she is, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 walking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 about in her nightie and she had a straw hat on and stick umbrella.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 This young woman did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why, what was the matter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Perhaps she were - she were imitating fellow. Aye. Aye, in her nightie, a straw hat and stick under her arm, she were w
alking about. Oh, think of funny things don't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What did she call your mother, how did she address your mother when she worked for your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well I - I couldn't really tell you. Yes, I was too young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Was the washing done at home or was it sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Oh no, we did our washing. Yes. I mean to say in them days you know - them - them people as had no husbands, they used to have to do some washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Take in washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 Oh yes, they used to that you know with rubbing board and p
eggy legs, you know, one half'd do and most likely see - if you - if you had no father they'd go - take a big basket, somebody'd give you a - a big basket full of clothes, a lively polly and a bit of soap and then when - they're washed you'd have take 'em
 back. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
You'd get about one and sixpence. Oh - aye - they're nothing like they're getting today. They - they - they got no help and - at Christmas time you did. If you had - you had no father you could go temperance hall at Christmastime and they'd give you 
a parcel and in Christmas week your mother'd get a bag of coal. That were once a year.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you remember hardship when your father died, did your mother have a very hard time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well you see, she - she - she's two bring up. She's us two to bring up. Yes. Aye, she'd us two to bring up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So she had a very hard time did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 But she turned out to the mill, she gave up the shop and turned out to the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh I mean, it didn't kill her. It didn't - she didn't die 'til she were eighty-six. Mum.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 But she gave up the shop when your dad died did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes. Yes, aye, that's right, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did your mother make or mend the family clothes, did she ever make your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes, she made our clothes, yes. Well bi
ggest part of the - the ladies at that time had to make their clothes. They had to be doctor, 'cos I mean they couldn't pay no doctor's bills, so I mean to say at that particular time really, Stothers of Atherton they were manufacturing chemists, they use
d - you could go and get a pint of quills, pint of penny royal or - all them little things, glycerin, castor oil, the lot, camphorated oil, you get 'em all in - in penn'orths as you get different kinds of pills like wind and water, backache all p}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 nny a time and that's what they had to use.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So your mother was doctor as well as clothes maker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Well every - every woman was. Every woman had to be doctor. And in them days they hadn't carpets on floor you know. They'd sand. Flags and sand. And as today t
he women of today, they tidy up at Friday, they say - I'm not cooking any more for anybody this week, I've tidied up. But at Friday you could see the old dutch over, they used to have dutch oven hung down cooking }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 cheese}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  and bacon and then they had bar acro
ss fire, you know, up on there, they used to have that - were on - that were at Friday when they'd done the cleaning and they used to - in fireplace they used to have any amount of - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 black}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  leaded things you know. And - if you - if you were - improving in statute, getting up a bit, you could have a steel stand. Like - if you had a steel stand you were a bit }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15296863\charrsid9517149 better}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 than somebody else. You were going up in the world if you had a steel stand, you'd gone - you'd gone above the black leader just now. Well you kept all - you - they were doing work cleaning all that tackle.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you ever know anybody who really went up in the world?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why do you think it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Up Farnworth I - I remember - I'll not mention his name. His - his father died
 when he was very young and they lived in Victoria Street. So there's only him and his mother now. So he starts going out - with a young fellow called Lewis, sells milk. And he goes and makes a few coppers having on and makes coppers where he could get. B
ut - but now he spends a lot of his time now at nights studying. And eventually he got to be the manager of two big mills up Farnworth, Yes. And he's living today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You think he did it through hard work then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 He - yes, he - well - it were - he - h
e had to do it through going to night classes. It weren't what - what he learned during the day. He had to go to night school - night schools got him, then we had another fellow as did very well. It were night school - them as went night school, it paid o
ff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you think it was possible to move up in the world in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Yes, it was - it was possible. It was possible. If you was good enough - a bit better than some - somebody else, you could get the job. So really you gong to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 night school}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 , yo
u are - kind of a foot in front of t'others aren't you. And - well it - he worked - manager of these two big mills and this other fellow, he went into whatsname business into - th'insurance business. And there's money made at the insurance business.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you ever remember anybody coming down in the world and what brought people down in the world in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Yes. Yes. I remember one fellow - he come down. He were - a - a coal - like a - you know these - the coal sidings at stations, there's a so 
and so, so and so agent. And - coal and he's really, he supplies nearly all mills with coal. Not kind of household coal is that - is -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Industrial coal?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Aye. He }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 sells}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  'em - in tens, not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 hundredweights}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 . Well this fellow, he had a good job like that. And - he got 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2893269 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  and they had a girl and - she died. So - he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2893269 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  a cousin now of - his late wife. And shed T.B. And they have a boy. And - they - her parents really hadn't - had some money and really they could have really have helped him you know, which they should have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why did he come down in the world though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
He - her expense. The expense of trying to get her right. It cost two hundred pound for a machine alone and a hundred pound in them days were a lot of money weren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What kind of machine was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 A breathing machine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 She had T.B.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Yes. And - so - his money got mixed up with - to - coal cash and - he had to - kind of - move off. So he - arrived at - all - Hoylake and West Kirby so he got a job the
re on railway. At Hoy - Hoylake and West Kirby, it's one railway and you worked guard, you give up tickets for get on train then you were guard and then when it stopped you took tickets off 'em again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So you went with the train, he did everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. So that were a fellow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So he came down in the world?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, that's where he come down, aye. Well I mean to say, he were nice fellow. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did anyone outside the home ever help your mother look after her home and family, relations or friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. No. No, you - you have a certain amount of pride - haven't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Say she was ill or confined to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh - oh, if - if you was ill or confined to bed in them days the neighbours were better than what they are today.
 Everybody - they're all in same boat. Everybody has to help one another - no money. Yes. That's where it is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What kind of things would they do when she was ill?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well they'd - at that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 particular time}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  they used - if it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 diarrhea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  we'-- say she
 was being plagued with they give her arrowroot. See the - it just depends what kind of - what she were ill with do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Would they help with the house and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes. They'd - they'd see - they'd get her out of bed and put her
 on a chair and shake her bed up and maker her comfortable and then they'd just }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 sweep}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 round or dust round and make her look nice and clean. Oh the neighbours in them days have to do, they had to help one another. They hadn't the money to pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you have relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you see much of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
I used to - down at Saturday morning and do one or two errands and - me auntie used give me me dinner. That's about all. I mean - at a - another auntie - crumbs, she used to
 - do you want a cup of tea? And at the time she says, I'm going to brew some. Every time we had a cup of tea it were cold. 'Cos - she were allus brewing on some tea that she'd - brewed before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So it would be very weak?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, she put a bit more tea in and then put his 'ere boiling water on. It were never really weren't tea you had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did your parents have a lot of friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, yes, they'd plenty - they'd plenty of friends. Yes. Oh I meant to say -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Where did they usually see them, did they come visiting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, - well they had to come visiting because me mother was busy. In shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did your mum and dad have the same friends or did they have separate friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well, they - they both had same friends, only me father, he spent
 a lot of time - playing - playing at - the piano you know. And then like for instance - this were - this were a racket. You - have a daughter and you want her to get her to play piano. Now - you go buy a piano and you know - you know my father - he's a -
 
really a good 'un so you says to yourself, I'll get John Tommy for 't' - pick me a piano. So she - she comes up and says, hello, John Tom, our so and so's going to learn play piano. Could you - will you find us a good one for us? Yes. Yes. Yes, this 'ere 
l
ady said, will you get a piano? So me father says, well you'll better give me a week or two like. I'll look round for a good 'un. But - he's done this job before, getting pianos for people so he used to come to a place called Yates in Moseley Street, they
 
were just piano dealers, secondhand piano dealers. So he - he comes now to Yates and he looks at pianos and he picks one what these 'ere people are going to have to have. So now he goes and tells these 'ere people come down like so and so night and we'll 
have a look at these pianos. He's not told them he'd picked one bear in mind. So - he's told - he's - he's picked this 'ere piano, he's got to know what price it were and he's told them put five pound on for his - for him. See?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 This was the racket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Racket. So - takes 'em down, now he does all this 'ere showmanship, takes top off, takes front off, pretends to be showing you all patching up piano you know, so on. You'd - make you - like drop 'em down there, let 'em put 'em on, you know kind of thin
g that dealers - some dealers do. Goes to another piano, does same thing again. Just showmanship. And he does like that. And - eeh that's a nice piano. Said, wait a bit, said, we're not - we're not just having two. We've not come to that piano as he yet -
 as he gets money on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So he'd take them along 'til they came to the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 So - they start saying we want that so he goes now to this}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9517149  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 piano as he's picked and does the same and he says, this is the one you want, this is the one you want. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So 
they say they have it, they treat me father for taking for taking them down and he get five pound off them. But that one used to say - says - I'll bet folk - I bet they don't half laugh at you - laugh at you. And he used to say, aye, he says, when they la
ugh at me, he says, they have to pay. He didn't mind being laughed at when he were being paid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you have a lot of friends invited to the house and how often did they come and did they come for meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well - yes, we - we had parties just like you have parties today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Tell me about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well I can't really just say but - I know we used to have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 parties}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  and that, we had sing-songs you see, with me father - as I told you, being a pianist he could play and his favourite, it were real funny
, it were that one called, Alice Whereat Though. Aye, he - he used to be that, and - then he'd say I mean to say, for instance and those boys and girls we just had parties at - that - different houses like they do today, you know. Oh yes, I mean that were
 - that were all right, you know but - the other parties a bit rough for children.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Were your father's and mother's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15296863\charrsid9517149 friend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  the same, did they share the same friends or did they have different ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well they had the same friends. Aye they had the same friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Could friends call in casually or did they have to have an invitation to come and see you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, no, they just - dropped in.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did your mum and dad go visiting friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, yes, yes. You just dropped in and they didn't - 
if they hadn't - if they hadn't enough for you well you - you just called a call, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You say when your parents got together with their friends they made music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Oh yes, yes, that - I mean, me father had to play and the people as could
 sing and have a right good do. For instance I mean I should say me father - had one of best dance bands there were. Yes. They were him, Jameson and Nelson and it was called Wolfendales Quadrill Band. It comprised a piano, violin and English concertina, n
ot this 'ere rough stuff you here - played today. Saxophone stuff. Sweet music. He used to have piano - English concertina and violin. You hear that for - for dancing. Well he - he - they - he called his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 Wolfendale's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 Quadrille}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 Band. But they danced different things than }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 quadrilles}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 . But just imagine how it would sound, that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one group or one class and some people belonging to another and can you tell me what the different classes were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, before 1918 I told you - Farnworth, Kearsley, Little Lever Walkden - they didn't like the Boltonions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 They - they thought that the Boltonians looked down their nose on them, som
eway or other. I mean, they used a lot - farm - farmers and all them people, they used a lot of dialect words. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You think this made a big difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. And the - the Boltonians seemed to - got a bit above the dialect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You think dialect divided people?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 It was divided by speech you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Yes, yes. Oh yes, I mean to say, see I mean to say, thought it up and - was think - to think I'm going again wit' shirt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What does that mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Wit' shirt. That mean
s getting wet through. Wet shirt. See I mean to say - these lot didn't know what they were talking about, a lot of farmers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So the Bolton people looked down on the Farnworth people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 That's what they imagined. For instance, Little Lever people - when I'm going back as a boy, they didn't eat meat or beef?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 They were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591642\charrsid9517149 fl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 ace}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  eaters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Beef.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh - flesh eaters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Flace. They called it flace. Ah, they're flace eaters. See? And then such as thing - there's Lev
er and Wringley, they're very clannish, very clannish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Hello - this is Mr Yates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What class would you think you belonged to as a child?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well me - with - me own - me very own self?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Your family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, and me own 
family. I thought we were as good as any - anybody else. Yes. I didn't - I never come - I never put myself down on bottom. I was as good as the top one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What sort of people would you think were in the same group as yourself?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 There's - there's no - it's - well - then as were in same group as me - wouldn't - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 succumb}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 to saying - just because we've not as much money as them we're not as good as them. That didn't make any difference. It's not the money. It's what you have up in your head.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You think this made the difference in the groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Yes. Yes. Oh yes, I mean to say, you - if you - if you keep hanging behind a few and say after you you'd always be at back. I'm not saying that I would walk on anybody or hurt anybody to get to top.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What would you say when you were a child were the people at the top, who would you consider were the people at the top?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well we - we used to think teachers were top. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Who else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And - factory owners. Yes. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Who were at the bottom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Workers. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Any special type of worker, did you think there was different classes amongst the workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well the - in that bit of the time they used to think coal work were at bottom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Coalman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Coaler. Coaler. The miner. That'
s what they used think you know 'cos we were dirty, you know. That's what they imagined. Yes. But you see - see - that - when I were a boy that - they used to come out on strike. One time they're out on strike for forty week and me father lent 'em his pia
no for forty }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 week}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
. But the trouble with the - the coalminer when he come out on strike, he always - at that particular time, he always come out in the summertime when people didn't want no coal. See, he were - he will - he lost from beginning. And that was 
it - and that - that - that particular time you know, if you - if you didn't work you'd nothing to eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 There was no strike pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. You had to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What happened to the miners families then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well the - they had to have soup kitchens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You remember soup kitchens do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 For miners, yes. And then like - this 'ere piano me father lent out to 'em, they - they had concerts. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 To raise money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. That were th'only thing they could do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you remember as 
a child being brought up to treat anybody different to the other, were you ever taught to touch your cap to anyone or call anyone sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well - well, we - we did that, we did that kind of - it come kind of natural. We did that to - doctor, th'headmaste
r or - our teachers or ladies like - when you - like for instance the - one lady, she were local woman and she lived in Campbell Street and - I used go round and - clean her hen coup out and then when I cleaned her hen coup out she'd ask me to swill the y
a
rd for her and then sometimes, she always reckoned to have - had headaches, you know, said, just go and get me a bowl of water, Joe. Put me some vinegar in. Now go and get that there cloth from over there. Put it in there. Squeeze it out. Come on now, put
 it over my forehead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 This is when you were a young boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did she give you money for doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. No. No, give me nothing, no, did she heck. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you remember anybody treating your parents in this way, showing respect to them, calling them sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh no, no, none of that. No, no, they didn't say that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Where you lived in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 Farnworth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  who were considered the most important people and did you come into contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 The most important people we
re really they were the - factory masters. No I mean, the biggest part of the factory masters - up Farnworth and I should say Bolton or anywhere, they seemed to run the - the Sunday schools. Yes. For instance, I went New Jerusalem, Kearsley. And - it were
 never really without money. Because such as Kershaws, and Briercliffes, they were factory owners, then was other people besides - there were Cookes, printers, and they all give money. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And they were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh - they keep the 
- they kept the place going. And it's - it was same with - there's - there's places gone now that were run with - with people like that but there's no people comes forward. There's no workers like then, they used to work a lot for Sunday schools although 
they were factory masters. Mrs Kershawe did a lot for Kearsley New Jerusalem. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 When you were a boy do you remember who the teachers mixed with, socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well they seemed to mix with one another teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What about the persons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Parsons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Who did they mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
They - well they seemed to be just individuals, they seemed to be - wedded to the church as they were. They spent all their time with their - churches and schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What about shopkeepers do you think they mixed with anyone special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
No, they had no time. No. I remember going and working there for a woman called Mrs Gilman in Market Street and she sent me all road wi' a truck with two loaves in, that was tuppence ha'penny, right from there to Long Ca
useway. Do you know there? Long Causeway, right from bottom of Egerton Street, shoving a truck with two small loaves in and then I - I used to have to go up - before I went school at morning call at dinner time and a call - after I come out of school for 
see if anything doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You used to do her errands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. So and take orders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 This was a part time job while you were at school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well you could call it that but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Was it to earn some spends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. I - I used to get paid 
for that. She used to pay me for it so she says, one day says, she's two big - two big - pair of scales - two big 'uns, brass 'uns, said now she says, I'm going to give you threepence a week extra if you clean these two big pair of scales.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So you did did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Did I? I started. You know what she give me for clean 'em with? Ash. Coal ash. Coal ash. Coal ash and water. For clean these 'ere brasses. Well - and I mean it's a grocery shop. She has Brasso and all like that as she could give me. But no,
 she didn't give me that. She - have to do it with - coal ash and - water. Well I does it here and cleans 'em and clean 'em. I couldn't get 'em - I couldn't get 'em - polished like with whatsname. So - so eventually I done 'em and done 'em and done 'em th
en I says, I've done 'em now Mrs Gilman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So you stopped doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Yes. I said - I says, I've done 'em now Mrs - Mrs Gilmore. I say, I'll come and have a look at 'em. She come have a looked at 'em and said, oh she says, you'll have to do these a
gain. So she - went out and I chewed it over, I says, I'm not. I'm finishing altogether here. So I went out and walked away from scales and I told me - me father were ill at time then, in Thorn Street and me mother was there. I says, I've left you. I said
,
 I'm not going back neither. I says, she only give me threepence - threepence a week extra, I cleaned two big pair of scales, I said, and just me - only ash for to clean 'em with. And then I shows 'em her and she says these will do. I've got to do 'em aga
i
n. - I says, I'm not going back. So - about eight o'clock that very night a knock comes at door. I runs upstairs you know. I knew who it were. Mrs Gilmore. So Mrs Gilmore comes in and she starts telling the - whatsname. She said now, you don't want let hi
m do that else he'll - else he - else he'll never do any good at all for you. You want make him to come back a working for me. And I said, I'm not coming back. I'm not coming back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you have to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And I didn't go back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What did you do with the threepence, was it for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Oh yes, that was spending money for me. Oh yes. You see - for instance, I mean for threepence, goodness gracious, I mean you could - get - boiled sweets tuppence a quarter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you get spends off your mum and dad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 A penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Every week did you get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What did you spend it on?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Well you see sometimes - you'd - you'd sneak down some back and get one or two matches and you'd get ha'penny packet of - Lucky Strike cigarettes. They were three - three for a ha'penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And you used to smoke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well - I sometimes used to smoke cane. You know, you - well, you - you just imitating th'older ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Not actually smoking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes you did. You - you - imitating. You just im
itated 'em. Yes. For instance, that bit of the time you see, a fellow he could get an ounce of tobacco, a packet of cigarettes and a box of matches and he'd have change out of sixpence. His tobacco's only threepence or threepence ha'penny, his matches ha'
penny. And - his cigarettes a penny for five. Woodbines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
When you were a child do you remember who the employers used to mix with socially? The mill managers and people like that, the people who employed you, do you remember who they mixed with socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well see I - I went to really - I were in - New }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 Jerusalem}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  boys ambulance brigade. They didn't believe in - fighting, New Jerusalem. But they did - they - they'd have an ambulance brigade and with -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What did the ambulance brigade do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well - if anybody got hurt we could put them - to - to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Like a St John Ambulance brigade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 That - oh style of St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 John's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  Ambulance. Yes. And we had - stretchers and all like that and - everything for first aid but we wouldn't - but they wouldn't have no - such as boys brigade fighting - battalions, no. No they had ambulance brigade. T.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 This New Jerusalem, this is where the bosses came didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 New - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you remember who the bosses worked with - who they mixed with in their spare time apart from coming to New Jerusalem?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Eeh I couldn't tell you. They'd have their own - managers - they'd have their own - they were managers you know, I daresay. They might - they might have been freemasons. I should say they were freemasons. They'd mix with freemasons, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Can you tell me what sort of people went to church and what sort of people went to chapel and did you ever notice a difference between church people and chapel people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well there were really no difference. Everybody as went to the different places thought they were - best.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And they were going to heaven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you notice any difference socially between church people and chapel people? Difference in their standards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No they - n
o, they all seemed same. But I remember a fellow, when I - a year older than me, I used - he used be going in for boxing and he had - seemed to take a - have a bit of fancy to me. His name was Tansy. And naturally he were Irish and he went to St }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 Gregory\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 . Now when St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 Gregory\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  had the new organ, you know, opening of the new organ, Tansy said to me, he says, I'll smuggle thee in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why, weren't you allowed in a Catholic church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 I'm no - I'm no Catholic. So he smuggled in so we go in and there - what was her name - Mon - Mon - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 Monsignor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  Dyan, they had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 Monsignor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  at St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 Gregory\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 
Monsignor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  Dyan, there he is coming up front under a canopy like and there's all them - holding this canopy like that and he's - and like kind of a - what you'd think a teapot with }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 incense}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  and he's coming all round like that you know while this 'ere organ's playing. And I were - thought, you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Was there a lot of prejudice between Protestants and Roman Catholics in Farnworth, do you remember it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, I didn't thi
nk there were a lot of prejudice. No I don't think a lot of prejudice. If there any prejudice it were Catholics. Catholics thought they were on the right way. I mean - they seemed to be only the - they seemed to a lot of us seems to be paying to get there
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Paying to get to heaven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Aye. Which they'll not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or do you think there were different standards of living or different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well the - the - 
the very - I told you - the very poor you see, the children of the very poor - it were a matter - always jam and bread and a pint pot of tea. Now them children when they come to about - eighteen - they'd not had the building up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you think this was the only difference though in the different groups in the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 That were - that were - that were a big difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 That was the only one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. The - the - the children of the poor didn't get the building up of the - one - class little bit class above them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Would there be a big difference in their homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
The - their homes used to be kept pretty clean because I told you, it was sand. And like for instance your back kitchen, you didn't put curtains up there, you made, whiting, you know, that whiting and you used to draw your curtains on window.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You painted them on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Whiting - with whiting. Yes. You didn't put curtains up. You - you put whiting on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 This was to save money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So there'd be different standards even in the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Oh yes that - that - I mean, some - some as had a bit more money, they'd have curtains up. But the poor people had whiting, they put whiting and made it look like a curtain, yes. Well they had that in - in back kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you think that one lot of people might feel superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh - oh yes, oh yes, they're always - you always get one or two, always get one or two thinks they're superior than you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 When you were a child why do you think they thought this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Because they had a little bit more money coming in than what you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Always money was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. It were money. Yes. They - and I think they could be dressed a bit better than you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you think there was a distinction between craftsmen and labourers and did you notice it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Oh yes - oh - oh yes, craftsmen and labourers, oh yes, I mean - labourer he had - he were labourer. He - I mean - the labourer - the joiner wouldn't let the labourer - not for - little piece of
 wood on and - what - on a job that he would do. He had to just lift a - and he took 'em off }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 him}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
. The - the labourer were a labourer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And you felt he was looked down on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. He were a labourer. He knew - and he - and he knew were labourer then.
 But the craftsmen in them days - they better craftsmen than what they have today. You look at their work, go back hundreds of years, look at their work as they done in churches and different places then look at these so called craftsmen we have today, no
, they're not in same - not at same street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You definitely notice a big difference between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes. So, I mean, where craftsmen them days - time didn't count. Time didn't count. He - he liked his - he liked his work so muc
h that he'd work all day. Honest. He -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You didn't think this applied to the labourer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Oh no, no, well you see, he - he's only working so many hours a day and then when his hours are up he's - he's gone. He wants to go and have a pint, but the craftsman - he was different being altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did he have a different standard of living to the labourer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh certainly he had. Certainly he had. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How would it show, in his home or his children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well now supposing say they were part
ing tonight, he wouldn't say - well - goodnight to him or good morning or good afternoon or - or supposing say his wife were ill or anything like that, when he come of morning he wouldn't say, well, how's wife, is she any better? No. He would - he was jus
t a number. Get me? Mere labourer. And he were a labourer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 He had to work hard for his money too did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh - he - he had to help carrying and that yes. Fetch me, carry me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And the craftsman had a much nicer home you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes, certainly, certainly. Certainly. But - they were craftsmen in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you think your mother and father had the same attitude to people in different groups, they both and the same attitude to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Well except me mother, me mother reall
y - she were - too much - too much confidence in other people. She'd go like this - she has a shop. She'll give you a book, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 For tick you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, she'd give you a book and she'd put it in. But she hadn't a book - checking agen you. A
nd I've known - that's there's books come in and there's been some rubbed out }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 which}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 no - tell mother that, oh they wouldn't do that. No. She thought everybody were as good as herself. But they did. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You got a lot of tick in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Was there a lot of poverty round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Yes, you see, I mean in them days there were pawn shops. Now - say you're - you - I mean, and the woman I - them days, she had to have the face. You can't - she had to have the face, she had to lie - you can't pay your rent. She has to tell }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 rent man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  she can't pay. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 Can't pay your grocer's bill. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 She has for tell the grocers, not t'husband, it's the lady as has to do it. So - what she does, it comes Sat'day. You see. No. Monday. Now we'll say you're living }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  a house like that, you - so your Sunday }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 clothes'll}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  walk Monday into pawnshop and your mother'll get so much on them. Sat'day dinner time your mother'll be going and getting 'em back for you so you can wear 'em at Sunday. And that's all you
 do, you only had them clothes on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And Monday they would go in again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Well you see, she got - she got so much but she had to pay. Yes. Like for instance - yes, like for instance there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  men like - now these - men, they - they mi
ght have a hundred pound we'll say, now with this hundred pound they can lend this now to these 'ere labourers or these people as hadn't much money under 'em, they might lend them a pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 This is when you were young you're talking about?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 
Now I'll lend you a pound for the week and I says to you, penny shillings. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
So when you give me that pound back at weekend you give me one pound one and eightpence. Now, it comes weekend, you say to me, I'm very sorry Joe, I can't give you that pound, 
or this, that, t'ther. I says, well, I says, give us th'interest. That's one and eightpence for now - you still owe me pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And this went on a lot did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Went on a lot. Aye. Aye. You always had pay th'interest. And still owed pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And one and eight would be a lot to a working man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes. Well you see, anybody having hundred pound and could lend hundred pound out, he'd no need work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you know anybody who did this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes, there were - there were men as had hundred pound you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Tell me about your mother and the shop and the tick and the people round about who had to go on tick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Yes. Well I mean say see - them like we left there that one shop - we went to - come to Bolton and we had a outdoor lic
ense at Tin - Tindall Street. Now - we sold snuff there and there were one old lady used to come, you could either - it were a - a canister like that, two different - tuppence - tuppence a - tuppence that big part and a penny this part you see, two. So he
r
 used to come and get pack of snuff. Now this old lady, she used come down there and - one Monday morning when she come into shop all her nose is blue. So mother says, what's wrong with your nose, it's all blue? Oh, her says, instead of taking snuff durin
g night, she says I must have been taking bag blue. Packet of bag blue you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 By mistake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Oh yes, I mean to say -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did a lot of the women take snuff in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did your mother sell a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, we sold a lot of snuff. Well the - the - they told me that all engineers used to take snuff.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why engineers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
It was - because they used to have to work to a thousand, you know, very fine work and they reckoned it were good for their eyesight. Yes, nearly all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 th'engineers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 had a snuff box. Now, when you went a being apprentice they'd tell you, get a snuff box and nearly all had snuff boxes, all t'engineers when I were a lad and they none of them wear glasses. They said as it were good thing for their eyesi
ght, 'cos you had to work to a thousand, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Would all the families round your mother's shop, would most of them be on tick or would it be only the very very poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes, they - they weren't all so poor as they wanted tick, you know, they
 weren't all so poor. They were only - like there is today, some can never get off their feet, you know. And perhaps, if - if you worked - give 'em start again they'd just be back again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You mean if your mother wrote it off they'd be as bad again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Yes, that's the - for instance, it were no good you putting the debt in the - debt collectors hands 'cos he wanted so much and - really you something and now that only thing you can do is don't let that woman have it again. Cross her out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 When you were a child do you remember anyone in your district being called a real lady or a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why do you think this was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. There were - I forget what her name were - she were a real lady because no matter when r what time o
f day anybody was sick and they needed any help, didn't matter where they went to or who they were, she'd always go. She did a lot for Farnworth, this one particular woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And she was always referred to as a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. And do you know, when she come to die there weren't one at her bedside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
It's just what they do. But she was a lady. Didn't matter who it were, what time of day it were, if they wanted help she'd give it. Without pay. But when it - when it come for her wanting help - nobody there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you ever remember anyone being called a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Gentleman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And why it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You - you - the only called on gentleman really when they give you something. That's all. Yes. If they give you nothing - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a special social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
No. No, no. She - me mother put herself no better than anybody else. 'Cos I'll tell you why. We - we had Caledonian in Vernon Street, pub you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you have a pub as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Caledonian. Well she got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2893269 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  again do you see. Yes. So we - we had a pub in Vernon Street, Caledonian, and - one fellow comes, he says - he says, yes, he says - you're landlady here aren't you? Well it made me mother blush like.
 She didn't like being called landlady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
I don't know. She didn't want be called different than anybody else. She said, well, she says, that's what they call me. What did he say? He said, well, he says, draw me a pint and be a boozers labourer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you live at the pub too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. A bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Tell me about the people, the types who used to come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh well, there was - they like you see - there were men who come in - in at front door, go into parlour, then there's ladies as know
s as that man's coming up front door, somebody else's wife, he's somebody else's husband and quite accidentally they meet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You're being sarcastic now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You mean it was arranged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 It were arranged, yes. So - but - there were quite a - a few doing this. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 
So me mother - the - these - these lot here one night and she went in and told them, stood up and says, now, she says, now that you're all in, says, I don't think any woman for coming in here with any - other woman's husband, I don't t
hank any man coming in here and meeting any other what'sname's wife. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 She says, 'cos these wives - these wives have got to know, they'll stop their husbands }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 from}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  coming Caley. You get me?;
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 In the district where you lived, suppose anyone did something 
that the rest of the community didn't approve of, how did they show their disapproval, suppose they did anything wrong that the people didn't like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Well for a bit they kind of tabooed them but - it eventually wore off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What was it usually for, what were the offences that people were very keen about and they didn't like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh - they didn't like misbehaviour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What type?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Like - knocking women down, knocking girls down or anything like that you know. They didn't like that, no. And
 I mean - the - they had - they had a decent code. They had a decent code, the code was good. Only like in any society you'll always get one or two who are - madams, no matter whether they're freemasons or not. All freemasons, all these other topnotchers,
 they - they're not all good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And they always showed their disapproval by sending them -?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 To Coventry. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Where you lived do you remember seeing a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes, oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did your mother ever frighten you by saying I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
No. Oh no, she never frightened you, no, no, I mean to say, they'd no need to frighten us, a policeman frightened us. Supposing we say we was stood at corner, about a lot of us he'd say, come on move on there. And if you didn't just jump to
 his - his 1 you know that big cape he had - whoosh. Knock you all down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You were afraid of him were you?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well you don't want to get knocked down did you. I remember he used to be - when I - when we lived up Halliwell in this street we had a - 
we - about forty of us of a gang and we used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 meet in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 Heriot
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  street on the corner step like - you know - and then sometimes we'd go and have a dance down on Walmsley. We had a fellow as - as could play concertina and we'd go there and dancing down ther
e.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What was the Walmsley, was it a field or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Back of bank where - Warburtons beds at - up top there. You can play cricket and football on it and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You were going to tell me about the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes. So - I don't kno
w, I weren't there this particular night but - there's - I don't know what they're doing but - the - this bobby, they used to call him Flannelfeet, you know, boots, boots, boots. Aye, Flannelfeet they called him and - whether they'd been calling him Flann
elfeet or what I don't know. But they all gone and he - he only caught one called Greenhouse and he - he were proper }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 knock-kneed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 like that, he couldn't walk, you know what I mean. He couldn't go, he collared him. So he says to, Greenhouse and he - gets him 
there, he starts having a scratch to him. And he just says now, if - if you'll tell - tell me husband - name of them others, he says, he - he'll - he'll not do anything to 'em. So Harry Greenhouse told them and they all got fined.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How do you think the policeman treated the people as a whole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes, yes, no, they - in them days they're a bit rough but - it were - it were - they weren't brainy, they were brawny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And you don't think he was very good with the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. No. I've not - I've - I've no place for the policemen in my time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Because I told you - you couldn't talk to one another on street before cape'd come round. And as I tell you, they were all brawn, no brain.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Now all these houses you had, were they always rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Yes, ours were always rented.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why did you move, why did you make all these moves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Well first of all you see I mean selling in shop weren't we. Now that shop, it - rent were bit too dear for us so we went in Pawn Street, we went - farther over. Then he died so now we go on Starcliffe in a house three shilling, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 At Starcliffe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. On Starcliffe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 This was a street was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. So that's three shilling a week there. And I - I leave now Francis Stree
t and goes to All Saints because I don't pay no school money at All Saints, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So you stayed there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Yes. Yes. No we'll say while we were on Starcliffe, now every Thursday we could get some very nice savoury ducks. Savoury ducks made of just li
ver and kidney, not like this stuff as you see lumps of it with big - covering over it, not like them. Different altogether. They were nothing like savoury ducks as we used to get from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 
Mather's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  at Thursday. Liver and kidney.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 In these houses that you lived in did you ever see your landlord and what did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Well - our landlord really - we didn't see landlord, you understand, the agent used come for landlord. All - biggest part of th'housed in them days, they were th'agent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What did you think of the agent, was he all right with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Oh yes. 'Cos you see he - he's - he weren't to blame. He - he had - he's only so much to do, he's only so much he can spend, it's the agent, see what I mean, as is looking after property - your pr
operty. See? You might have about twenty-forty houses, now you - you put them in the hands of an agent and this agent sends a rent collector, do see? Now - Seymours; if she were on it she'd be soft and they'd want anything doing she'd be doing it. As she 
wants some return back off her property and she's paying tow of 'em isn't she. So they have to keep it down haven't they, so as they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So you're }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 trying}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  to say you couldn't always get the jobs does you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh no. No, no. No, because - the lady
 had to have so much into stop her money kind of thing. So - if some - if there's so much property wanted mending like in a year somebody'd have to be missed. There'd only be able to spend so much. Else the lady'd have - lady'd be - living in a house and 
she'd be - out of pocket. Won't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you ever remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet and what did you feel about this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, I - I don't think parents ever had any struggle because me mother were a - always a worker. You know how I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You said your father was never out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Oh no. And them my mother said like, if it comes to eating bread and butter she can enjoy bread and butter just like she would if she were having chicken.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 She never had to go anywhere for help for anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
No. No - Guardians, no, so I can't anything about guardians. But they used to say that - like you and people used to be took away, mental, that - well they used to - I think they used to council - I think councillor
 Matthews, well I think he used to come about Friday and when he come about Friday - you - you were going in a mental home all right. I mean, that's the - it's - might - we'll say - might be about ten years now I saw a case, ten year back, that's not a lo
ng time is it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you ever see one as a child though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. Ten years ago there were a lady, she'd money bear in mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did your father never help your mother at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Not at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did he never help with your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, they'd no time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did he never help undress you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
No, did he beck, oh no, not likely. He'd sooner drink a pint of beer. Tell me stories. Oh no. I - for instance, I remember one day - mother said, oh we'll go
 up Blackpool for half a day. So she give me a shilling. We're only just staring off now, he says her going to give me this 'ere shilling he says, he says, give it me. Took shilling off me. So when we arrived in Blackpool, first thing he does he goes in s
o
me beer hotel and has a drink out of my shilling. So when we go on sands I keep looking at him, I think when's he going to give me shilling back. Mother says - what - what's thou keep staring at thee for? And I said, dad's - dad's took the shilling. He co
mes, he says you know, we're coming back home, we're back home for tea. So - so - she says, if we're - if were to come to Blackpool for half a day and thou has for to take shilling off lad well - it's not worth us coming.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And she brought you home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did your father ever mend your shoes or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
No, no, no, he didn't, no, he - he'd only - he only - only started drinking beer at twenty-five years of age you know. He'd never touched any before then. But after than he made up for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you have jobs to do about the house as a boy, did you have to help your sister or did she help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, no me sister were - five years younger than me. No, see she were only five and - I remember - making a swing for her at yard 
- bottom you know. And I put some flags under like so if she fell like she wouldn't fall so far. Aye, it broke, she fall and broke her little finger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you have jobs to do for your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. Oh - only errand or two. That's all. So - we take 
her to Doctor Ramsey, Great Lever. He were surgeon. So - he sets this 'ere little finger and then when he sent his bill it was ten and sixpence. So mother - took - the money and says to him, tell you what, lot of money isn't it, ten and sixpence for setti
ng a little finger? He says, it's ten and sixpence a limb. He said, if she broke her leg, broke her arm it would only be ten and sixpence. Ten and sixpence a limb. So a little finger's a limb.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you have to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 When you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Oh yes, that's right, yes, yes. I remember time they put me to bed one Sunday - eeh it were light but - and I got up and they weren't in and when they come back I was sit on step at front. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What time did you have to go to bed, do you remember when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 I must have gone bed early that time 'cos it were proper light you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you always have to go to bed early though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well, no, sometimes they'd give us a privilege. If they'd company. A bit yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Who put you to bed, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 We seemed to put ourself to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Who put you to bed when you were too tiny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh - me mother. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Not the lady who helped in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, me mother always put us to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 She just helped your mother round the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Eeh now, where did I - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 oh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  - in't sink. In't sink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You bathed how often, once a month did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Yes. Aye, it were in't' sink, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How often did you change clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh no - I should say we'd change 'em about once a month. But they didn't get so dirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You weren't in a dirty area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. No. Once a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Where did the family have their meals when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 In - in th'house part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 In the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, in th'house. Th'house. Th'house - shop, house, kitchen where chip shop is. We have it in th'house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 That was the middle room?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Yes, we always eat in that room and I don't know how it were but every Sunday - I used to think as I were entitled to it, after I'd had me dinner at home at Sunday I used go and get a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 saucer}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  and march right ove
r to a lady called Mrs Baker for me rice pudding. And then at t'other side there were a lady called Miss Heath and I thought she were th'only lady as could make proper potato cakes because she made 'em like a triangle. And I went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How did your mother cook, did she have a range or did she cook by gas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 She had a range - fire - coal. Coal range. Oh they'd coal ranges then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 When was breakfast eaten and how many people were present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh eight o'clock. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Was your father there and all - he family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh no, me father had gone to his work at seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So he'd have his breakfast first and then you'd have it afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, he had his breakfast - he had to get his own breakfast ready and then go on to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Tell me what you used to have for meals in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well we - we used -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Tell me about all this marvellous food you were telling me about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh well I mean to say that - it weren't really - fancy stuff, it was - good plain food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What did you have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 We had - egg and bacon like you have. Oh yes. Eggs were cheap. They weren't above a penny you know. And when }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 pancake}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  Tuesdays used to come they were twenty-four for a shilling. And - the - if you bought - a packet of self risi
ng flour and some'at else I think they'd give you a - the egg. You know, instead of - some people buy packet of pancake mixture. Well now you make your own, get flour, egg, milk, whatsit, you can make your own do you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You always had bacon and egg for breakfast every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What kind of dinners did you have and what kind of teas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Oh at dinner time we'd - we used to have - whatsname - a bit of meat and vegetables and potatoes, we were very lucky you know. We were lucky. Sometimes we'd have - fish and chips. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How many times a week would you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15086350\charrsid9517149 about}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 - well you see, we used - we used to buy it for se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
l it, you know, we used to sell lot of pork chops, we used to get 'em that's right from Mark Schofield, he used to come round in a little - yes, and bring boiled hams, ordinary hams, bacon and - the lot. Mark Schofield.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So you'd have a lot of meat wouldn't you?
