 give you some lettuce and young onions and a bit of mustard and then he'd put you a pansy in your coat. Aye. I mean to say there were a fellow called Maurice, he looked after the way - bowling green. Now he could go - good celery. You know. Big 'uns. The
y
 used to - get 'em grow a then put each - and you slap papers round you know. Yes. Now in celery see, you got a celery, your mother'd say, now - you must eat the green because it make your hair curl. The heart - your father. Your father - no, only father 
could eat hearts. You - you could eat the outside, - the green ones, they made your hair curl.
