\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 ray}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  they'd eat the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 ray}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 ray}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  water she'd - she'd bathe her husband's strained back with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did it work?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Oh they always did that, yes. See, at that particular time as I'm going back to you know what price you pay for silver }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 ray}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  now don't you. Well silver }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 ray}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  were a cheap fish then and people as used to like it and they'd have stood round cart, they always waited 'til t'other people got away. Cod fish were - were main fish then at sixpence a pound, silver }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 ray}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  fourpence. But when anybody we
re ill and doctor had advised them have a bit of something light, he always had fish and it always were cod fish. Not silver hake. But really the finest fish on the board, because it were cheap, nobody'd buy it, it was the herring. The herring. There's mo
re }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 nutriment}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Talking about the mining community in Farnworth, what was the main amusement, how did they amuse themselves as a group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well they - they - only used to - no, it were always wrestling - or - no, nearly always wrestling, boxing and piggy playing. Used to be }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 champion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  piggy players.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What's piggy playing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 It's - it's a wooden thing like that wi' a - and like a nose on. Well you used to have to carry your own brick with you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What was the brick for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 For put your - you
r - piggy on, see. And then you have a stick, see, so you're - you're allowed so many rises, you know, for - a practice. Now, you see, you put that piggy on your brick then you go like that and then you - whoosh - you know, you - you hit that piggy as far
 as you can. It all depends - on - on who's knocked it farthest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Would the miners all play this too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Would they play it for money, would it be a gambling game?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Yes, yes, they were - there were champion piggy player. Oh yes. Well there - there were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 jumpers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 - they all seemed to be jumpers, runners in them days, there's jumpers, runners, piggy players, boxers, the - that's what they spent their time in. Yes. And I mean to say, for instance - if you were a runner and a goo
d runner and I comes to you and says, hey - will duck? That's mean - that - I don't win. How - how much would it be worth? Said, so much. Give it him. And do you know what he'd do after that you know, he'd go and win and - and win some money himself and -
 
knowing very well that you daren't say as he'd been bribed. Right twisters. Aye, right twisters. Best people in the world and yet - they were wash-outs. Get your children out as a quick as you can, don't bother what they're going to finish up with at twen
ty-one or when they get to a man. Get all as you can out of 'em now. Make use of them. Don't bother about how they're going to go on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you think as a whole though people were cruel with their children when you were young?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well they were - they
 were - I reckon they were cruel than and the - the - the - well they - they - they made - made - made all that money out of them you see for instance there were lots of young men at twenty-one or twenty-two, they might - they never got no farther than - 
side piecing. Sixteen and tenpence a week and they were getting }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2893269 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 on sixteen and tenpence a week. The wives'd be a - a doffer or a - tenter or something like that and they'd both have to work. Well you see then it comes you see that - lot of 'em - the
y had pretty big families so what did they do. They open a little - they open a little shop in their - in their house do you see. And they buy a lot of stuff from Co-op which is giving three shilling in pound divi, see. So what they do, they get this thre
e shilling in pound divi off what they buy and feed their big family and what they've left see they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 sell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 to the people see and copper two above th'odds. And made the divi on it as well. But eventually they save enough money up that they can buy a little sho
p of their own. And there's - there many a one as got a little shop of their own through getting the divi off this stuff as they sold to other people after they'd - yes, yes. Oh yes, they did. Well that's the only way they could do. Yes, oh yes, a big fam
i
ly you see, now I mean to say, you might as well get it wholesale mightn't you. But see, well you can get three shilling pound that's not doing so bad is it. So you feed your own family and get three shillings pound. Now you sell it to these other people 
a
nd you put a - a ha'penny or so on th'articles you see. And so you get - get a little bit more besides. So at finish - at them times - well when - a pound were worth a lot of money then. Hundred pounds - if you'd had hundred pound then you'd had a - you w
o
uldn't have had any need to work if you'd been a money lender. At a penny shilling. If you get a hundred pound out - at one and eightpence a time coming in. And the - yes, hundred one and eightpences, think of it. Now fellow comes and says, I'm sorry, but
 
- I can't pay that there pound back this week. Well, he says, give me th'interest. And - you going to have to keep giving him that interest while you have that pound, you - nothing goes off your pound. So if you'd had hundred pound then you'd had no need 
work. Hundred pound.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What was your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 My first job - it were - in Greens in Devon Street. They made cardboard. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How old were you when you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Thirteen. They - they made cardboard. That were like lots of brown papers stuck together with sowing and then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What's sowing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Flour and water. Sowing. And - then they have a big cylinders just going round gradually like that so that you take your boarding now and you put these 'ere - all this 'ere stuck stuff you kno
w, put papers on because it's going to be cardboard when it comes out and you go right across there like that and come back like that to - 'cos it's always moving you know and by time it - they come out at t'other end it's - dried and ready and then we ha
d to put 'em through kind of a squeezer. Then after that they used to cut 'em into a certain size and then from there they used to go somewhere else and they used to be made for work - what they call - Philip Millers as makes patterns you know. And -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 In the printing - they used to be printed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, they - they were holes cut in it and they used to make - different kinds of patterns on like for bedspreads or anything like that. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Cardboard for pattern making?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How much did you get at this job, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Yes, I did very well there, I got more there than anywhere. They - if - for you - you got seven shilling a week there and those - they were only - paying five shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How did you get this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 A pal of mine - as worked there. Yes. He said, would I like go and work at Greens and he took me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How did you like the job, did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, but it - it were bit of dead end. It would have been a dead end so eventually I gets chance now of goin
g into Coross's warehouse under fellow called Mr Parkes or going on Farnworth and Kearsley Co-op milk so I choose Farnworth and Kearsley Co-op milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And you stayed there for life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 I stayed there for fifty-three year. Fifty-seven year. Fifty-seven year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 The first job you were at, did you get on all right with the people you worked with, did you like them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, yes, yes. Oh - oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What was your boss like, did he treat you O.K?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well they - they kind of never bothered with you. No, you just went, did your work and - everybody just walked about. Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Tell me about the Co-op, did you like the people you worked with there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes, yes. Oh yes. I mean at Farnworth Co-op when I were boy at that particular time you know, oh 
it just like home. You know what I mean. You were happy. You were happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What was your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 wage there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 , do you remember, and your hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well it - it'd be five - it were five shilling a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What time did you start and what time did you finish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Oh - see now - well you see, I - I'm on milk. I'd be turning out at seven o'clock wouldn't I. Yes. I turned out at seven o'clock and then - at that particular time we used come in at dinner time. And then - once during week - oh we had clean our can
s you know. And then we'd had clean our cart once a week and then we have to come back again at - at th'afternoon for a bit of a teatime delivery. Yes, oh yes. But - there weren't a lot of them but there were teatime delivery.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And you worked Saturday and Sunday did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you get holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes, you got holidays with pay, you got holiday when you were sick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Always from being a boy did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Yes. Yes. Well you see, you get all of this - with sic
k because somebody else - they always have a odd man or two about on chance anybody goes sick, see, so he had to come and do a job beside job he were doing see, so - they weren't taking anybody - they didn't take anybody on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you ever have to serve an apprenticeship for any of your jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Were you ever in a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes. I have - I have a medal upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Was this before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. I have a medal upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Tell me what you got this medal for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 See it's at that paper there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you take part in any of the trade union activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, no, not - not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 This was just for long membership was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 This medal was for thirty years continuous membership?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 But you didn't take part in any of its activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. No. Oh - oh yes, I went to a meeting once when the - got together, you know. I were in caf\'e9
 at time and - we're trying to get so many days a week do you see on - on a rota. A rota. For us that - have a - a days holiday. 'Cos you see when you're in caf\'e9
 you worked - you worked Wednesday morning and then you worked all Saturday, see, and then on top of that you had parties, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You used to take milk to parties did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes. Oh yes. And during the war you see we used to have lot of freemasons coming because they used -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Was this the second war or the first war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Second war. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What hours did you work at your first job when you were at this cardboard place, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh we - we used start at - at seven o'clock, then we come away at - half past twelve. Half past one 'til half past five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you get holidays with pay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well - well I weren't there that long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you work Saturdays or Sundays there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, didn't - no, no Saturday - yes, Saturday morning. Oh yes, but not Sundays. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What hours would you work Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well 'til dinner time. Yes. No, it were only on Co-op milk where you worked Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 When you were at school did you ever have a little job outside school to earn some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 coppers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Yes, I - I had - I decided I'd - sell papers. So - I - as soon as I come out of A1 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 Saints}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  - not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 school time}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
, I used to whip up to a - a fellow as sold papers wh
olesale at bottom of Darley Street. Now papers were then they were ha'penny each so that meant for a dozen I'd get sixpence. So what I'd used pay for I used pay fourpence a dozen for 'em and when I'd sold 'em I'd got sixpence a dozen, so, oh that - that w
e
re what we called thirty-three and a third percent weren't it. So - and then at Saturday I seemed to - you see - they - they were a penny, you know, buffs and that, well - football finals and you used pay eightpence a dozen for them and get a shilling, se
e
. So, I used to get these papers and run round streets shouting you know - these 'ere papers and - this were - time of Boer War I'm talking about now you know. Yes. Boer War because - I always wanted someone be - on placards for - to whatsname - so I coul
d sell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149  \lquote em}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
. I - so - yes, such as like - D Webb in a tight corner. General Bother nearly captured or anything like that, you know, so and so, you know, relief of Mafeking or Pretoria or - sommat like that. But you always wanted something on - on a poster th
en people'd by.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You carried a poster with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, no. No. But these - these paper shops had 'em out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 When you made your profit did you keep it yourself or did you give some to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 I give it me mother. Yes. And then shed give us some spending money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How much spending money did you get from your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 I - I think - well, sixpence. Well you see sixpence were a lot of money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well - I - now and again I used save up and I used buy 
my little cousin a present. You know them there little but pot things and all like that. They used to be about sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you never spend any of it on yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes, used to buy - I told you, I used to buy }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 toffees}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 , I used to buy them ha'penny packets of cigarettes you know. Lucky Star. Tree for ha'penny, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you feel that there was a great division of interest among workers before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 If - if somebody got a little bit higher than anybody else they showed you. They let you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What do you mean by getting a big higher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Like suppose - say - he - he's foreman of you and a few others. You know he's foreman. You don't open your mouth. You didn't open their mouths in them days you know like they do today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You mean they daren't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
That's right. 'Cos you - you'd soon get sacked. Oh yes. You had to do what you were told. Whether it were something in your line of job or not. You just had to do what you told 'cos if you didn't they'd say, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 who\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  boss here? Me or thee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You felt it was very hard work in those days did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Oh yes, you had to do what you were told. And if you did what you were told, well, you got on very nice with boss. But if you - if you thought boss were kind of laying it on and you compl
ained - well you'd be out. If they don't want do it there's plenty others'll do it, see that's where it is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you feel there was a big difference between trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh there's - there - for instance, I mean - the trai
ned - the trained craftsman of my time were far superior than this lot. This lot aren't in the same class, you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 look}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 at some of these 'ere staircases they've made. Look at inside these churches with all that work as is in it. And how much did it cost, about threepence an hour. We hadn't - we haven't the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 
they haven't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  the craftsmen today like then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
But before 1918 did you think there was a big difference between trained craftsmen and ordinary workers, did you notice a big difference between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 They - they - a trained craftsman - he didn't interfere with you. No. He was - he was - more deeply in his work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 More interested in his work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. He didn't really - he hadn't time to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you think it gave him a better standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh he had - oh certainly, the craftsman were the - were the highest paid man. He had - he had a labourer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And it gave him a better standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Yes. Yes. But - the work - the work the craftsmen did in them days better than stuf
f now you see. This stuff's all made with machinery. Not - not hand turned you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What would be the difference in the homes between a trained craftsman and an ordinary worker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Would it show a lot in their homes do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well he could be a bit irritable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 In the standard of living in his home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Oh yes, oh yes, oh yes, oh yes, oh yes, I mean to say, we - we'll say your mother might make you a cake, they'd buy a sandwich and have a pound tin of salmon on table and fruit and that. See. You'd finish up with apple if you were lucky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why did you say he was irritable, what were you going to say about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well - well - see - they're so engrossed in their work - that they don't want their mind - interrupted. 
They have - they've all their mind on the job and if you ask them about anything else bar what they're doing - they don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You think the trained craftsmen loved their work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes, oh - he worked. Oh he liked doing good work, craftsman. Oh 
yes. It'd break his heart if he'd a - if it turned some work out as is worth turning out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 When you started full time work do you think it changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes, it does do, it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15296863\charrsid9517149 does}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  change your life, for instance I meant o say it's funny you see, you start working. Now - the - you go and work at somewhere and by about time you're fifteen you come to conclusion that it - that you - can do job }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15296863\charrsid9517149 better}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  than boss. What boss is telling you to do you - you can't see anything - 
anything about it. You think, well, I - you do it this way, you do it that way, you - you know better than him. But when it come to be forty you find that you don't know anything then. But at fifteen and sixteen, you - aye, you knew it all. But when you g
et older you find out you know really nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 When you were a boy did your parents ever take you visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Now and again like we'd go to - to me - me grandfather you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Who took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Me mother. Me -
 me grandfather, did I tell you about me - how me grandfather did? Well - well me grandfather - he had - lobe of his car cut off with a tub of coal in pit. Yes. And - the - at that particular time as they're performing operations they made a very good job
 
of his ear and people come for see it for quite miles around. It was such a good job. Now - he doesn't go back in pit. What he does now, he starts - going and knocking up. That's you - knock - start about five - four o'clock in the morning knocking people
 up for to go to work you know and - after that he used to go on the tip and - pick bits of iron, string and tin. He used help fellow you know to - to scrap merchants and this tin he used to get, he - at home he had - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 punch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  - punches with numbers on you kno
w, with numbers on. So he used to cut these 'ere tins now into a kind of a - a medallion. Nock a hole in it, put a piece of string in and - you know - tie it, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  then he put a number on. Well had sell them now to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 coalers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 for a penny each. So - for - if th
ey were get injured or killed that number now they know who they are. Yes. Coalers used to have these 'ere on 'em. When they went down pit they used - used to have these 'ere and grandfather used to make 'em out of string he'd got off tip, tin he'd got of
f tip, all as he wanted were a punch, see. Well - about four punches do you see. Making one, two three four, you see, could make any number - well one - go up to ten.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Suppose a man was killed down the pit how would they know him, would he leave his number at the top?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Yes, well - they - they - yes, they - he - he - he had a registered number. They were all kind of - this - everyman had different number and they could tell with this 'ere thing as he had on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And he liked that better than working down the pit did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
He made more money. He worked - he - he - he bought a house. It's on - it's - you go by it - by Long Causeway. As you go up Albert Road, Long Causeway's down here and the pit of New Brick at top there, hundred and fifty, there 
- my grandfather bought that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Out of the money he made on the tip?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Yes. And when he died he left over three hundred pound, which were lot of money. And he didn't work. He made more money without going working with stuff as people didn't want - j
unk. Junk. Like - for instance - everybody as has junk there's some other person wants that junk. It is so. So I mean to say, for instance, if he - if you wanted to sell something and he thought he could make another shilling or two on it he'd bought it o
ff you, he'd buy. He always had his eye open for a bargain. But not for work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 He didn't like work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
He didn't bother at it after he'd had that part of his whatsname chopped off. And - his father - used to be a very big fellow and he used to have bets on for what they called - spanning. Spanning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What's spanning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Yes. Well - you go again wall and you send your hands cut like that - a big span and he - he reckoned to be right big fellow and he had matches for what they called spanning. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Surely he'd always win if he was so big?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well there's other big people besides him you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 They came from other districts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes. Yes, they get people from all over. Oh yes. They didn't dare put - they didn't put him up against 
thin 'uns. No. They - they - I mean they - them as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14436562\charrsid9517149 put}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  - were putting their money down, they saw they had a big fellow too. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And this would be the miners again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. Aye. Oh yes. They - all kinds of roads of earning livings then. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What other ways were there in your grandfather's day apart from working on the tip?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
I don't - well that's the only thing as I know about. Grandfather did that you see. And - he made it - payable. Aye. And - he'd be about seventy-nine when he died so h
e didn't do so bad out of it. No. Well - he kept me - he kept his - his and other son - me uncle. As - his wife, they had two children and his wife had T.B. and that particular time they had to eat a lot of liver, you know. Yes. Yes, eat a lot of liver, y
ou know - liver with blood. Yes. But it didn't cure 'em. It's just a myth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did she go into hospital with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. No, didn't go into hospital then, she didn't do into hospital.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Then she would pass it onto the rest of the family surely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
No. No she didn't. Do you know, there were a lady down Hall Lane, a Mrs Yates, and she had about - she - she had T.B., she had ten children and she only reared one and she died in the gutter, drunk. These other nine children besides - you know - besides B
essie which lived, they - sacrificed their young lives for her to live, they sucked it from her. Mrs Yates. And there were only one in ten, and that were Bessie.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 And she died in the gutter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, eventually. Drunk. Now - well she'd T.B. All of these nine children had sucked the T.B. and it killed them, know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 That was dreadful wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You said you always went with your mother to your grandfather's, did you never go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well - I tell you - me father were always busy. He were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 at some}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  pub or some - if they were having a dance or a party he were always at them, do you see, playing piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you ever go away on Bank Holidays with your father or mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well I don't know whether they had Bank Holiday or not, he worked on railway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you go away for a holiday at all when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. We used take th'old tin box you know with us. You know, these - yes, everybody took with pem what they're going to eat for week,
 you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 In the tin box?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. You - you - everybody took their food with 'em. And they only paid then a shilling a night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 For a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well each individual a shilling a night. So I mean to say, if there's six of you it'd be six shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Which was a lot those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 It weren't a lot. No. Not - not when you look at prices today, if you wanted - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Where did you used to go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Blackpool.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Always Blackpool?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What did you do when you got there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Well - used play about sand and that and then we - we - we used to lodge in a place called Bonny Street, yes, Blackpool, and that were where all fisher people lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Fishermen you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. And what's there I - I can - I can see now t'husb
and coming now with bags of shrimps, you know, and boiling 'em and when they come with these bags of shrimps they're just like - kittle crawling things as crawls all about sands - dark. Well - now they put 'em in - in a big pan and boil 'em and they go pi
nk. And then all - her children now are on table now taking shells off so they can - sold.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Who would sell them the next day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 They'd sell - they'd - they'd sell 'em to some shop or something like that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 This was at Blackpool?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Were you ever taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
No - she used - she took me once for a suit. At Beatty Brothers. And I - she didn't let me pick me own suit, she picked it for me. She bought one of them there little Eton round hats you know and a big collar and a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 Norfolk}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  suit, which means knickerbockers. And I said, I'm not having them. Them knickerbockers because I know what lads says about lads as have knickerbockers.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What did they say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 They used said did their business in 'em - and it - it fell to bottom of legs and never dropped down, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 So you didn't want to wear those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
No. I knew what lads said about 'em. I had to have 'em. I took parcel down with me to go somewhere but I had pick it up, I had to have it too. I weren't pleased about that, I knowed what all lads'd be saying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did they say it when you wore it, did they make fun of you when you wore them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 I've forgot now but - I knew they would be. If they didn't say it to me they'd be saying it to one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How did you get on with hour sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh - I got on champion with me sister. She always used keep mauling after me, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 She made a fuss of you did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 If I went anywhere she wanted be with me. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 
I remember one time going from - Campbell Str
eet, I was going an errand and perhaps I go for some boiled ham or something, I don't know how, but I'm going into Edgerton Street and she were following as usual and as I'm going across Edgerton Street a pop cart with two big horses in is coming - its co
me up Hall Lane, and - it's a bit of a brew there now - well he's got speed up and he's prancing away up - up - up - up - hey, our Clare finishes under th'horses and under cart.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Was she badly hurt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, never hurt at all. Th'horses never touched h
er. And cart never touched her. So - I - I picked her up and - I took her into a little kind of baby linen shop, Mrs Shorts, and then we went home. Weren't she lucky?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you always play with her or did you play with other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh no, I didn't really play with her, she played with girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you play with neighbours children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. I mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 We used to play - like - dropping th'handerchief and one thing and another, be my fair lady and all like that, j
ust like they do today. And - we used to be boys and girls do you see and then you'd drop handkerchief or something like that and then when it come a certain time you used to have a May Queen. Used to have a May Queen. Oh yes. Like, for instance, I might 
have - have a white pinny on and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 a bit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 of a white hat on and - a rolling pin in me hand. I'd be a baker, see. And - yes, and then - they had different things like that. Then - our - Queens she'd have a bit of a tail, somebody's old curtains and - we'd go al
ong you know and - we - we'd be collecting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Knocking at doors and collecting?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. And then when we - thought we got enough we had a tea party with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you play in your house or in the street or where?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh in't' street. Oh yes, yo
u had - I mean - us - us boys, you had girl friends just then like - like - you liked some girls better than other girls. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played or did you get into trouble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh no, I could get dirty, didn't make no difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Could you play with anyone you pleased or did your parents stop you playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, oh no, I could play with anybody. No, they didn't stop me - didn't - not like some - kind of - only play with so and so and play wit
h so and so. Got like - Campbell Street and Leigh Street and Lawn Street, they were big division.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Well them in Campbell Street were more like a middle class people. Them in Leigh Street and - Lawn Street, they were poor class. You know what I mean? They were poor class. They were poor class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Was there a big difference in the types of homes they had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes. Difference in types of homes and the difference - there were a dividing line with people too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You mean they wouldn't bother with each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. Not them in Campbell Street wouldn't bother with them in Leigh Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you ever go in both the types of homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes. I tell you, I used go to Mrs Baker's every Sunday for me rice pudding you know, that were i
n Leigh Street. I used - after I'd had me dinner at home, I never had no sweet at home. I used get a saucer and go over to Mrs Baker's. I liked her rice pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What would the poor homes be like, very badly furnished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well they had - they hadn'
t much furniture and I told you they'd sand on't' - but they were clean. And - if they could afford any of them black leaded things they got 'em. They - they used to seem to - pride in them black leaded things - or - brasses, as they had to rub their head
 off. They seemed to like them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You mean to keep them clean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Yes. But when you got a - a steel stand as you could put in fireplace, you know, you didn't really sit on it much, you were moving up. Oh - you had a stand, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736813\charrsid9517149 t'others}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  hadn't. They'd onl
y black lead things now you had a stand. You were another foot higher up than them. Just - just - in the poor class it's just same as in middle class. Some were little bit higher than t'others. Just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you ever go in middle class homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, I told you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 This lady with the rice pudding, was she middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, she were a poor woman. I told you, she's in Leigh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You were telling me about a lady who used to make you wring out clothes, was she middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Aye, she
 - oh aye, she were a Mrs Jakes, she were Liverpool woman and she's a terrible temper too. Yes. I mean, I don't know what - a Mrs Thompson had done, very nice lady, Mrs Thompson but she must have done something. Mrs Jakes nearly scalped her. Started pulli
ng her hair out. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 That wasn't very middle class was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
No. And then - one time - during night there's somebody - about at - Jake's you know, thought they were burglars. Who gets up and gets hold of poker. Not Mr Jakes. Mrs Jakes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Was there someone there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No, there weren't anybody but had she'd have hit 'em. And that were a woman who's I used to clean her hen coup out for her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What type of house did she have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh very nice.
