\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well I - I got on with her all right because I didn't bother w' her much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You left well alone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, I left well - I didn't bother with her much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you and your wife have a lot of friends and did you entertain?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes, yes, oh yes,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You did have a lot of friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did they come to your home a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 For meals and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh be - it - it were ever open door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 They didn't have to wait for an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. Just drop in. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Were they your friends or your wife's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
The - they're both our friends. They're both our - they're both our friends but I had a - we had a - a little cousin, her name were Molly and - when we used see Molly come we used say to mot
her - hey, Molly's here, get some potato hash made. She liked potato hash.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you and your wife go out visiting a lot or did they always come to your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh - no, no we went out visiting a lot, yes. For instance, every Christmas we used to g
o up New Bury and this 'ere fellow, Mr Wood, they used to have quite a lot of people go, he used get a little keg of beer in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How would you amuse yourself when you were with friends, would you sing or play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well - well we played - we play 
- played games like you do you know. You know, just all - all same games and they - they didn't buy a turkey. Mrs Wood used to boil a ham, a twelve pound ham. And she were cutting off it all time. You get me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 What kind of games would it be when you were with friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 They - they liked guessing games and all - you know - but they're very good, ayes, the guessing games, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 When you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2893269 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 did you ever feel you had a hard job to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes. It - it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 How did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well I - it come about this - we're paying }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15296863\charrsid9517149 this}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  'ere mortgage off again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You've bought this house have you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes. We're paying this mortgage off 'ere and - I don't know how it were but it - it come one quarter that - we're a 
bit tight. So - I goes down to corporation, you know, and mentioned it to 'em. Oh - I'll have to find it, they want it you know, keep their books straight you know and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15296863\charrsid9517149 t'other}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 . So - someway another we scraped enough and I took it down. And do you know what they said when I took it down? Where had I got it from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 they thought you'd pinched it or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Aye. Where had I got it from.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Looking back on your life what would you say was the difference between your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2893269 Married}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  life and your childhood, how did things change from being young as a boy and growing up and being }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2893269 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  and having a home of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well - well from being a boy and growing up - I've always tried - to do - right. So - I've always made it me business I'm not going to be
 pushed around. If anybody starts pushing me around they're going to know. I don't push them around, they're not going to push me around and I don't care who they are, I don't care what size they are but they're not going to push me around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you feel your life improved as you got older, materially, do you think they were good old days or bad old days when you were a child?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Well as far - I - I couldn't really grumble. You know what I mean? I mean - really, I could have been born in a better fam
ily, you understand that. That's why I say - you - and me don't owe anything to anybody. It's not our fault we're here is it. So - we don't - owe anything to anybody such as thing - well, hers brought him up and he hasn't done this and ought do that. That
's not it. Is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you think they were good old days when you were a boy or bad old days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
They - they - well as far as children were concerned they were bad old days because - as I told you - they put 'em in all blind alley jobs. See, in that p
articular time everybody - all good jobs - were in certain families. But - yes, such as Farnworth. Them - them in council, it might be - we'll say }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15296863\charrsid9517149 Morgan\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 . He were Registrar of births and deaths, he died. His son now drops in as if he should do, you get me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 You think this was done deliberately?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 No. There - there seemed to be a clique. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15296863\charrsid9517149 
Now Entwhistle, there always used to be a Entwhistle over at Fire Brigade at Albert Road at that time. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, he always were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15296863\charrsid9517149 
superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 . You get me. And then - t
hey all - thought it were kind of closed shop. When - if the father died or father retired they thought one of the family should come in and get that job. Now, the - the council eventually come }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14436562\charrsid9517149 on}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149  - Frank Morgan were working at Co-op in our office. His fat
her died and he left our place and took that on. But they told him - they - at this game you don't - at this game. But - as he'd had war service - they let him have it. And I know that one councillor - Labour councillor - no wonder I don't care about poli
tics - his son has to go to school twelve month and there's a vacancy and it's not going to be filled until that lad's twelve - left school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Was this before 1918 or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 That were - second world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 When you were a boy do you ever remember any prejudice between Roman Catholics and Church of England people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Oh yes. Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Did you ever see this in Farnworth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Yes, it is so, yes, I mean, it is so. 'Cos like - when - when I were at Farnworth there were fellow called S
warbury, he a big Catholic and as you know I - I'm not a big Christian and - they talk about so and so. I says, get away, I says, there you are I says, carrying - what you call virgin lady. Huh, I said, I know what they'd call her today. I says - I said, 
there you are, lugging her about, I says. And got on from one thing and another and do you know what he said? He started }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15296863\charrsid9517149 talking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 about having big families. He says, they're Catholics you know, I told him I says, why are you always getting big families? He s
ays, oh, he says, we'll stop majority one of these days he says, he says, if we can't keep 'em somebody else will. So - the Catholics can't grumble at these - Pakistani's or Indians about it because they were the instigators of this one. Big families.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1250662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 Do you remember prejudice against Irish at all in jobs and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2235835 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
Yes. Oh yes. Yes. That - I know - as well like - for instance - there were one where we - and one day he said to me he said, I'll knife you. He says, if I get - me Spanish 
blood up - so I got hold of - you - you've seen them little drawers like that in old }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15296863\charrsid9517149 grocers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9849632\charrsid9517149 
 shop with knob on? I just got hold of his head like that and bumped it there. I says, see like that there, I'll put that knob in your head next time that you menti
on knives to me, you and your Spanish blood. Spanish blood. Certainly. Yes, I mean, that's like - these Irish people, they want - they're in all papers, they want to - tell you what to do and what not to do
